I have implemented the Adobe PDF Embed API via the header of a page so that we can render a PDF file on page that resides at <http://pdp.box.com|pdp.box.com>.  &lt;script src="<https://documentservices.adobe.com/view-sdk/viewer.js>"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;

The rendering works fine for .pdf files in the HS Files, but when they are external inks such as <https://pdp.box.com/shared/static/jl93l9ztlbzospz16yc6qojt8xd2j3ag.pdf>, I GET
``` CORS Mising Allow Origin```
Shouldn't I be able to address this with `Access-Control-Allow-Origin : <http://pdp.box.com|pdp.box.com>` in the HS header? When I attempt to add it, HS says the "There is invalid HTML or HubL in the Head HTML". Is my syntax not right?
